Here **issue** is **same name of json key** :

    {
        gigs:data[0], // &lt;----- gigs
        gigs:data[1]  // &lt;----- gigs
    }

If you use same name key then it **will get override by the last one**. 

-----------------

The solution to this is to use the **different key name** or merge 2 results into one

    {
        gigs:data[0],
        gigs2:data[1]  // &lt;----- Change this key name gigs2
    }

    // OR

    {
         gigs: [ ...data[0] , ...data[1] ] // &lt;--- Merge result into one
    }

